                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the south base of the central shrine in the Naṭanapādēśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Kulōttuṅga I. Year 42: 1111-12 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This record registers the gift of 50 sheep by Kaḷappāḷaṉ Śellaiyaṉ Tōṇṇambi of Eydamendūr, for the merit of his wife Umai Naṅgai, for half a perpetual lamp to god Tirukkaṇṇīśvaram-uḍaiya Mahādēva in Śōḻakulavallinallūr in Paṭṭāṉpākkai-nāḍu in Gaṅgaikoṇḍaśōḻa-vaḷanāḍu. </p>						
                            
                        </summary>
